### isSimpleEnoughValueToCommitHelper() {#a64280af8a02343f452989f8d3fb62653}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static bool isSimpleEnoughValueToCommitHelper (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/constant">Constant</a> &#42; C, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallptrsetimpl">SmallPtrSetImpl</a>&lt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/constant">Constant</a> &#42; &gt; &amp; SimpleConstants, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/datalayout">DataLayout</a> &amp; DL)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Return true if the specified constant can be handled by the code generator.

We don&#39;t want to generate something like: void &#42;X = &amp;X/42; because the code generator doesn&#39;t have a relocation that can handle that.

This function should be called if C was not found (but just got inserted) in SimpleConstants to avoid having to rescan the same constants all the time.

Definition at line <a href="#l00057">57</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/transforms/lib/transforms/utils/evaluator-cpp">Evaluator.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

</SectionDefinition>
